courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the semester, students should:
- understand key concepts and theories of sound studies and their significance in contemporary China;
- understand the relationship between sound and culture in contemporary China;
- be able to apply sound studies theories and methodologies to analyse sonic culture in contemporary China.

After completing the course, students should:

- be equipped with the essential techniques to examine the artistic features of any artwork;
- have a basic understanding of Chinese art history and aesthetics since 1900;
- be able to critically analyze various aesthetic and artistic issues in Chinese art, and to participate in relevant scholarly debates.

On completion of this course, successful students will be able to
1. define a topic in Chinese Studies and conduct research into that topic using appropriate skills and resources;
2. for those with knowledge of the Chinese language: acquire Chinese language sources from libraries or internet databases;
3. make constructive use of influential theoretical paradigms.

By the end of the semester, students should:

1. * be able to critically understand key concepts related to the selected topics;
* be able to apply relevant theoretical frameworks to issues of the selected topics in contemporary China;
* be able to learn research methods to collect and analyze data relevant to selected topics;
* be able to locate and use secondary sources relevant to selected topics.

